{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FveJcRN3vNxiEQFGzzdti7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Murmuration Quality Optimization — Autoresearch Program\n     2→\n     3→## Objective\n     4→Maximize the murmuration quality score (0-1) which measures how closely the simulation matches real starling murmuration behavior based on empirical measurements from Cavagna, Ballerini, and Attanasi et al.\n     5→\n     6→## The Score\n     7→The composite score combines 5 metrics from real murmurations:\n     8→- **Cohesion ratio** (target >0.90): fraction of boids with 5+ of 7 neighbors\n     9→- **Velocity correlation** (target 0.75-0.95): avg alignment with neighbors (1.0 = too static)\n    10→- **Aspect ratio** (target 2-5): flock elongation (1=sphere, bad; 3-4=ideal)\n    11→- **Density uniformity** (target CV<0.5): uniform spacing, not clumpy\n    12→- **Shape dynamics** (target 0.05-0.2): flock is actively morphing, not frozen\n    13→\n    14→**Current baseline score: ~0.70**\n    15→\n    16→## The Loop\n    17→1. Read the current `shader.wgsl` and `index.html` (Murmuration preset values)\n    18→2. Pick ONE parameter change to try\n    19→3. Edit the file(s)\n    20→4. `git add shader.wgsl index.html && git commit -m \"experiment: <description>\"`\n    21→5. Run: `python3 evaluate.py`\n    22→6. Parse the last line of stdout for `score: X.XXXX`\n    23→7. If score > previous best → KEEP, append to results.tsv\n    24→8. If score ≤ previous best → `git revert --no-edit HEAD`, append to results.tsv\n    25→9. REPEAT. Do NOT pause. Loop until interrupted.\n    26→\n    27→## What You Can Edit\n    28→- `shader.wgsl` — hardcoded constants in the flock() function:\n    29→  - `K_NEIGHBORS` (line ~127): try 5, 6, 7, 8\n    30→  - Gravity: `new_vel.y -= 0.03` — try 0.0 to 0.1\n    31→  - Center-seeking: `normalize(to_center) * 0.08` — try 0.0 to 0.3\n    32→  - Roost attractor: `normalize(to_roost) * 0.3` — try 0.1 to 1.0\n    33→  - Roost orbit speed: `f32(params.frame_count) * 0.002` — try 0.001 to 0.01\n    34→  - Roost orbit radius: `params.sphere_radius * 0.4` — try 0.2 to 0.6\n    35→  - Noise amplitude: the `* 0.15` — try 0.0 to 0.3\n    36→  - Separation multiplier: `* 2.0` — try 1.0 to 4.0\n    37→- `index.html` — Murmuration preset values (the agent reads these via benchmark.ts):\n    38→  - visualRange, separationDist, alignFactor, cohesionFactor, separationFactor\n    39→  - maxSpeed, minSpeed, turnFactor, smoothing, sphereRadius\n    40→\n    41→## What You CANNOT Edit\n    42→- `benchmark.ts`, `evaluate.py` — locked evaluation\n    43→- `render.wgsl`, `renderer.js` — rendering\n    44→- `simulation.js` — compute pipeline setup\n    45→- `program.md` — only humans edit this\n    46→\n    47→## CRITICAL: git revert\n    48→Use `git revert --no-edit HEAD` to undo failed experiments. NOT `git reset --hard`.\n    49→\n    50→## Results Tracking\n    51→Append to results.tsv: `<experiment_number>\\t<score>\\t<description>\\t<kept|reverted>`\n    52→\n    53→## Optimization Strategy\n    54→The score has 5 components. Focus on whichever is weakest:\n    55→- Low cohesion → increase cohesionFactor, reduce sphereRadius, increase visualRange\n    56→- Low velocity corr → increase alignFactor\n    57→- Bad aspect ratio → adjust gravity, roost attractor shape\n    58→- High density CV → adjust separationFactor, K_NEIGHBORS\n    59→- Low dynamics → increase roost speed, noise, reduce smoothing\n    60→\n    61→Try ONE change at a time. Small increments. The evaluation takes ~90 seconds.\n    62→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b0e04ab-0a04-4fdc-bf69-142a37b30a0b","uuid":"36e52e17-c57e-43e0-80db-23531283e250","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:29:24.524Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/aaronlemke/AI/Murmuration/program.md","content":"# Murmuration Quality Optimization — Autoresearch Program\n\n## Objective\nMaximize the murmuration quality score (0-1) which measures how closely the simulation matches real starling murmuration behavior based on empirical measurements from Cavagna, Ballerini, and Attanasi et al.\n\n## The Score\nThe composite score combines 5 metrics from real murmurations:\n- **Cohesion ratio** (target >0.90): fraction of boids with 5+ of 7 neighbors\n- **Velocity correlation** (target 0.75-0.95): avg alignment with neighbors (1.0 = too static)\n- **Aspect ratio** (target 2-5): flock elongation (1=sphere, bad; 3-4=ideal)\n- **Density uniformity** (target CV<0.5): uniform spacing, not clumpy\n- **Shape dynamics** (target 0.05-0.2): flock is actively morphing, not frozen\n\n**Current baseline score: ~0.70**\n\n## The Loop\n1. Read the current `shader.wgsl` and `index.html` (Murmuration preset values)\n2. Pick ONE parameter change to try\n3. Edit the file(s)\n4. `git add shader.wgsl index.html && git commit -m \"experiment: <description>\"`\n5. Run: `python3 evaluate.py`\n6. Parse the last line of stdout for `score: X.XXXX`\n7. If score > previous best → KEEP, append to results.tsv\n8. If score ≤ previous best → `git revert --no-edit HEAD`, append to results.tsv\n9. REPEAT. Do NOT pause. Loop until interrupted.\n\n## What You Can Edit\n- `shader.wgsl` — hardcoded constants in the flock() function:\n  - `K_NEIGHBORS` (line ~127): try 5, 6, 7, 8\n  - Gravity: `new_vel.y -= 0.03` — try 0.0 to 0.1\n  - Center-seeking: `normalize(to_center) * 0.08` — try 0.0 to 0.3\n  - Roost attractor: `normalize(to_roost) * 0.3` — try 0.1 to 1.0\n  - Roost orbit speed: `f32(params.frame_count) * 0.002` — try 0.001 to 0.01\n  - Roost orbit radius: `params.sphere_radius * 0.4` — try 0.2 to 0.6\n  - Noise amplitude: the `* 0.15` — try 0.0 to 0.3\n  - Separation multiplier: `* 2.0` — try 1.0 to 4.0\n- `index.html` — Murmuration preset values (the agent reads these via benchmark.ts):\n  - visualRange, separationDist, alignFactor, cohesionFactor, separationFactor\n  - maxSpeed, minSpeed, turnFactor, smoothing, sphereRadius\n\n## What You CANNOT Edit\n- `benchmark.ts`, `evaluate.py` — locked evaluation\n- `render.wgsl`, `renderer.js` — rendering\n- `simulation.js` — compute pipeline setup\n- `program.md` — only humans edit this\n\n## CRITICAL: git revert\nUse `git revert --no-edit HEAD` to undo failed experiments. NOT `git reset --hard`.\n\n## Results Tracking\nAppend to results.tsv: `<experiment_number>\\t<score>\\t<description>\\t<kept|reverted>`\n\n## Optimization Strategy\nThe score has 5 components. Focus on whichever is weakest:\n- Low cohesion → increase cohesionFactor, reduce sphereRadius, increase visualRange\n- Low velocity corr → increase alignFactor\n- Bad aspect ratio → adjust gravity, roost attractor shape\n- High density CV → adjust separationFactor, K_NEIGHBORS\n- Low dynamics → increase roost speed, noise, reduce smoothing\n\nTry ONE change at a time. Small increments. The evaluation takes ~90 seconds.\n","numLines":62,"startLine":1,"totalLines":62}}}
